The '''VIII Corps''' of the [[Ottoman Empire]] ([[Turkish language|Turkish]]: ''Sekizinci Kolordu'') was formed in the early 20th Century during Ottoman military reforms.

==Formations==
===Order of Battle, 1911 ===
With further reorganizations of the Ottoman Army, to include the creation of corps level headquarters, by 1911 the VIII Corps was headquartered in [[Damascus]]. The Corps before the [[First Balkan War]] in 1911 was structured as such:<ref>Edward J. Erickson, ''Defeat in Detail, The Ottoman Army in the Balkans, 1912<U+2013>1913'', Westport, Praeger, 2003, p. 379.</ref>

*VIII Corps, [[Damascus]]
**[[25th Infantry Division (Ottoman Empire)|25th Infantry Division]], [[Daraa|Dera]]
***73rd Infantry Regiment, Dera
***74th Infantry Regiment, [[As-Suwayda|Suveydiye]]
***75th Infantry Regiment, [[Al Karak|Kerek]]
***25th Rifle Battalion, [[Ma'an|Maan]]
***25th Division Band, Dera<br>
**[[26th Infantry Division (Ottoman Empire)|26th Infantry Division]], [[Aleppo|Halep]]
***76th Infantry Regiment, Halep
***77th Infantry Regiment, [[Kahramanmara<U+015F>|Mara<U+015F>]]
***78th Infantry Regiment, [[Adana]]
***26th Rifle Battalion, Halep
***26th Field Artillery Regiment, Halep
***26th Division Band, Halep<br>
**[[27th Infantry Division (Ottoman Empire)|27th Infantry Division]], [[Beirut|Beyrut]]
***79th Infantry Regiment, [[Haifa|Hayfa]]
***80th Infantry Regiment, Beyrut
***81st Infantry Regiment, [[Jerusalem|Kud<U+00FC>s]]
***27st Rifle Battalion, [[Mesiha]]
***27st Division Band, Beyrut

